#: ../../I/I-see-no-X-here-.rst:5
msgid "I see no X here."
msgstr "I see no X here."

#: ../../I/I-see-no-X-here-.rst:7
msgid ""
"Hackers (and the interactive computer games they write) traditionally favor "
"this slightly marked usage over other possible equivalents such as \"There's"
" no X here!\" or \"X is missing.\" or \"Where's the X?\". This goes back to "
"the original PDP-10 :ref:`ADVENT`\\, which would respond in this wise if you"
" asked it to do something involving an object not present at your location "
"in the game."
msgstr ""
"ハッカー(および彼らが書くインタラクティブなコンピュータゲーム)は伝統的に、「There's no X here!」「X is "
"missing.」「Where's the X?」といった他の同等の表現よりも、このやや風変わりな言い回しを好む。これは元々のPDP-10版\\ "
":ref:`ADVENT`\\ "
"にさかのぼる。ADVENTは、ゲーム内で自分がいる場所に存在しないオブジェクトに関わる何かをするよう求めると、このように応答したのである。"
